<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1893,1999]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,152,938]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
This species and 
<taxonomicName box="[360,574,1894,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichthyomorpha">
<emphasis box="[360,574,1894,1919]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">C. ichthyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been quite thoroughly confused in the literature, though based on structure of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[457,541,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 16" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1099,1123]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,194,1073]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[156,1431,194,1075]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 16, Aedeagus of Chrysobothris and Xenorhipis. 11, Chrysobothris chiriquita; 12, C. ichthyomorpha; 13, C. thomsoni, Colombia; 14, same, Trinidad; 15, Xenorhipis bajacalifornica, dorsal; 16, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274596/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[511,541,1933,1959]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
) and female last ventrite (
<figureCitation box="[845,914,1933,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,182,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1431,182,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5, Chrysobothris Adult dorsal habitus: 3, C. chiriquita, Costa Rica; 4, C. ichthyomorpha, Mexico; 5, same, Panama. 6 – 8, female last abdominal ventrite: 6, C. chiriquita; 7, C. ichthyomorpha; 8, C. thomsoni. 9, C. lucifera, holotype. 10, C. collaris (= C. thomsoni), holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274595/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[899,914,1933,1959]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) probably it is closer to 
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1347,1934,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiriquita">
<emphasis box="[1197,1347,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">C. chiriquita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In my opinion, those characters are the only sure way to distinguish the three species being treated here, although distribution can be helpful. Unlike 
<taxonomicName box="[566,778,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichthyomorpha">
<emphasis box="[566,778,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. ichthyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(q.v.), the hind angles of the pronotum were found to be bright coppery-red in all specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[604,746,192,217]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomsoni">
<emphasis box="[604,746,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. thomsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that I examined. Additionally, the apical foveae in the latter are usually separate, while in 
<taxonomicName box="[543,756,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichthyomorpha">
<emphasis box="[543,756,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. ichthyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are usually joined; however, this is far from being a uniformly reliable character. The female 
<typeStatus box="[659,762,272,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[781,869,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,182,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[166,1431,182,1902]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 10. 3 – 5, Chrysobothris Adult dorsal habitus: 3, C. chiriquita, Costa Rica; 4, C. ichthyomorpha, Mexico; 5, same, Panama. 6 – 8, female last abdominal ventrite: 6, C. chiriquita; 7, C. ichthyomorpha; 8, C. thomsoni. 9, C. lucifera, holotype. 10, C. collaris (= C. thomsoni), holotype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274595/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[839,869,272,298]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1051,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis box="[924,1051,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. collaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[1070,1163,272,298]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">MNHN</collectionCode>
) is 
<quantity box="[1212,1320,272,298]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.26" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="12.6">12.6 mm</quantity>
long and labeled “Caracas, Sallé (green)/Th. 
<typeStatus box="[576,650,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
<collectionCode box="[576,650,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">TYPE</collectionCode>
</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[659,750,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collaris">Collaris</taxonomicName>
(LaF. M.ss, 
<typeStatus box="[902,960,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Type</typeStatus>
Th./Ex. Musaeo 
<collectionCode box="[1169,1262,312,338]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">JAMES</collectionCode>
THOMSON.” This specimen is atypical in that the median elytral green spots are coalesced into a fascia, and the apical fascia is divided into distinct spots. I examined specimens as follows: 
<collectingCountry box="[982,1142,392,418]" name="Colombia" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">COLOMBIA</collectingCountry>
, Valle de Cauca, 
<collectionCode box="[1352,1432,392,418]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">CLBC</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[151,245,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">MNMS</collectionCode>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[264,441,432,458]" name="Venezuela" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">VENEZUELA</collectingCountry>
, Aragua: Rancho Grande, Portachuelo, 
<quantity box="[910,1002,432,458]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[1014,1108,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1952-09-06">
<number box="[1014,1028,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="6.0">6</number>
-IX- 
<number box="[1078,1108,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="52.0">52</number>
</date>
&amp; 
<date box="[1148,1232,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1979-05-08">
<number box="[1148,1161,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="8.0">8</number>
-V- 
<number box="[1201,1232,432,458]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="79.0">79</number>
</date>
; Pozo Diablo, cr. Maracay, 
<date box="[266,366,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1955-02-27">
<number box="[266,297,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="27.0">27</number>
-II- 
<number box="[336,366,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="55.0">55</number>
</date>
; El Limón, 
<date box="[505,617,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1970-06-15">
<number box="[505,533,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="15.0">15</number>
-VI- 
<number box="[585,617,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="70.0">70</number>
</date>
; Bolivar: km 
<number box="[777,821,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="125.0">125</number>
El Dorado-Santa Elena, 
<quantity box="[1112,1203,472,498]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[1214,1327,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1967-09-26">
<number box="[1214,1245,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="26.0">26</number>
-IX- 
<number box="[1297,1327,472,498]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="67.0">67</number>
</date>
. D.F., El Valle, 
<date box="[226,313,512,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1942-10-06">
<number box="[226,240,512,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="6.0">6</number>
-X- 
<number box="[281,313,512,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="42.0">42</number>
</date>
, 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33834" box="[325,404,512,538]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33834" name="Museo del Instituto de Zoologia Agricola Francisco Fernandez Yepez" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">MIZA</collectionCode>
. 
<collectingCountry box="[422,567,512,538]" name="Ecuador" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">ECUADOR</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[578,628,512,538]" name="Lithuania" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Lita</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectionCode box="[640,732,512,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">BMNH</collectionCode>
. All of the specimens (
<collectionCode box="[1006,1098,512,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">BMNH</collectionCode>
) cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Waterhouse" box="[1213,1437,512,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" refString="Waterhouse, C. O. (1887) Biologia Centrali-Americana, Insecta, Coleoptera, Buprestidae, Volume 3, part 1, 33 - 48, p. iii." type="book chapter" year="1887">
Waterhouse (
<number box="[1366,1427,512,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1887.0">1887</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
are instead 
<taxonomicName box="[285,496,552,577]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ichthyomorpha">
<emphasis box="[285,496,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. ichthyomorpha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is a specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[826,898,552,578]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(no other data) in 
<collectionCode box="[1117,1200,552,578]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/hj12-2xm7" name="National Museum Prague" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">NMPC</collectionCode>
that is questionably this species. Based on the structure of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[769,856,592,618]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 16" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1099,1123]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,194,1073]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[156,1431,194,1075]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 16, Aedeagus of Chrysobothris and Xenorhipis. 11, Chrysobothris chiriquita; 12, C. ichthyomorpha; 13, C. thomsoni, Colombia; 14, same, Trinidad; 15, Xenorhipis bajacalifornica, dorsal; 16, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274596/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Fig. 
<number box="[824,856,592,618]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
), specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1070,1170,592,618]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
may represent another taxon; however, other characters, including the female last ventrite, match well to 
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1276,632,657]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomsoni">
<emphasis box="[1132,1276,632,657]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. thomsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have seen additional examples from Guaico (Sangre Grande), 
<date box="[766,922,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1969-08-07" valueMax="1969-08-26" valueMin="1969-08-07">
<number box="[766,820,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="16.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="7.0">7-26</number>
-VIII- 
<number box="[892,922,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="69.0">69</number>
</date>
, 
<collectionCode box="[935,1015,672,698]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">CLBC</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[1028,1105,672,698]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/jekt-x82m" name="Florida State Collection of Arthropods, The Museum of Entomology" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">FSCA</collectionCode>
; 
<quantity box="[1118,1199,672,698]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0460736" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" unit="mi" value="6.5">6.5 mi</quantity>
. post, Maracas Bay, 
<number box="[151,181,712,738]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="80.0">80</number>
- 
<date box="[189,282,712,738]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="1969-08">
VIII- 
<number box="[252,282,712,738]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" value="69.0">69</number>
</date>
, 
<collectionCode box="[295,372,712,738]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/jekt-x82m" name="Florida State Collection of Arthropods, The Museum of Entomology" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">FSCA</collectionCode>
. Besides the three species just discussed, there are others in this group in this group from South 
<collectingCountry box="[227,332,752,778]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">America</collectingCountry>
; however, I have seen only 
<taxonomicName authority="Gory" authorityName="Gory" box="[660,920,752,778]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridifasciata">
<emphasis box="[660,852,752,777]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. viridifasciata</emphasis>
Gory
</taxonomicName>
(photo of 
<typeStatus box="[1045,1098,752,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
, 
